- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with redundancy in propositional formulae, which is a topic in mathematical logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses complexity results and algorithms for checking redundancy and finding irredundant equivalent subsets. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper analyzes the complexity of the problems related to redundancy in 2CNF and Horn formulae. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possibility as redundancy elimination is a common technique in automated reasoning and theorem proving. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possibility as the paper deals with propositional formulae and their properties, which is a topic in discrete mathematics.
